<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/16601ARPMPTNDDCJCLRDPBTPKBJMLVCDR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Jon Faddis and CapU Jazz Ensembles";
  schema:description """
	Jon Faddis is a renowned trumpeter, conductor, composer and educator widely recognized as the protégé and musical heir to jazz icon Dizzy Gillespie. Faddis closely mirrored Gillespie's virtuoso style early in his career, becoming a close friend and mentee, and later serving as the musical director for several of Dizzy's tribute bands, including Dizzy Gillespie Alumni All-Stars.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For this concert, Faddis brings his Dizzy charts to be performed by both large and small CapU Jazz ensembles.  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Faddis played with Lionel Hampton and Charles Mingus in his early career, before becoming a noted studio musician in New York. Faddis’ distinctive trumpet – his incredible range and control is often referred to as “stratospheric”– appears on hundreds of records, from James Brown to Paul Simon. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In the mid-1980s, he left the studios to continue to pursue his solo career, which resulted in albums such as <span class=\"ItalicText\">Legacy, Into the Faddisphere</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">Hornucopia</span>. Gillespie declared of Faddis, “He’s the best ever, including me!”  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Faddis has taught at the Conservatory of Music at Purchase College-SUNY in New York since 1999. Remaining true to the tradition of honoring mentors, he also leads master classes, clinics and workshops around the world; he often will bring promising students along to his gigs and allow the students to sit in and also has produced a number of CDs for up-and-coming musicians.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://youtu.be/r6bIf5UlRUY?si=RSLy2rTJHPTj0039\">Watch Video of Jon Here</a>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-27T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/files/16c11dae-481a-4f84-aaec-d3024b75b838.jpg>;
