<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/13201ACQQNNPSNRJMNQRQRCSJCCGPQLHJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Ron DiLauro Sextet ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Celebration of one of the greatest jazz albums of all time.</h1><span><br/></span>The Montreal-based Ron Di Lauro Sextet is known for its sophisticated arrangements and emotive performances, as well as for the incredibly astute homage it pays to Miles Davis’ iconic album <span class=\"ItalicText\">Kind of Blue</span>. Widely regarded as one of the greatest jazz albums of all time, the record’s modal-jazz cool revolutionized the genre in 1959. Ron Di Lauro Sextet’s interpretation captures the spirit while infusing it with a modern sensibility, blending its timeless qualities with the individual voices of the musicians.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ron Di Lauro, a highly skilled and seasoned jazz trumpeter, is recognized for his ability to blend intricate technical mastery with an emotive, soulful performance style. Leading the sextet, he channels the essence of Davis, whose playing was characterized by lyrical beauty and understated yet profound adventurism. The sextet’s lineup includes trumpet, saxophone (tenor and alto), bass, drums, and piano, with each member contributing to the rich, nuanced sound of the ensemble. Their performances are marked by expressive solos, intricate harmonies, and an overall reverence for the original work.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Yet perhaps the most significant aspect of this tribute is the sextet’s ability to evoke the spirit of the 1959 recording while still remaining firmly rooted in the present. Di Lauro and his group acknowledge that <span class=\"ItalicText\">Kind of Blue</span> was not just a moment in time, but a monumental shift in the world of jazz. Through their dedication to the material and their own creativity, the sextet not only celebrates this pivotal album but also reminds the audience of its relevance in today’s jazz scene.  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Musicians:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Ron Di Lauro - trumpet<span><br/></span>Jean-Pierre Zanella - alto sax<span><br/></span>André Leroux - tenor sax<span><br/></span>Taurey Butler - piano<span><br/></span>Ira Coleman - bass<span><br/></span>Martin Auguste - drums<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=58o0High22I\">Watch Video</a></h2><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">This concert is part of North Shore Jazz (June 19-28), presented by BlueShore at CapU in partnership with Vancouver International Jazz Festival.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-22T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/files/369e14af-a3fe-4466-8945-4626b2345883.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/location/601APNNMRMBJQQPBSCNQGQHGKKCRPSSGN>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/organization/blueshore-financial-centre-for-the-performing-arts>;
  schema:offers _:6ffa29f358cb41bc8eef5cfc78901d955849;
  schema:keywords "North Shore Jazz";
  schema:duration "PT120M";
  schema:endDate "2026-06-22T21:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

